<!-- §9 What is a cooling gel eye mask -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is a Cooling Gel Eye Mask?</h2>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A cooling gel eye mask is a wearable device containing sealed, reusable gel that's stored in the refrigerator and applied directly to the under-eye area. Unlike ice packs or cold spoons, it's designed to conform to your face shape, distribute cooling evenly, and protect delicate eye skin from direct ice contact.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Cooling Gel Eye Mask uses cold therapy—thermotherapy's opposite—to constrict blood vessels, reduce inflammation, and promote lymphatic drainage. This decreases puffiness and the appearance of dark circles. The gel stays cold for approximately 20 minutes, giving you a full treatment window without re-freezing or ice pack maintenance.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">It's become a sleepmaxxing staple because it delivers immediate, visible results without serums, needles, or ongoing costs. Perfect for morning routines, beauty sleep preparation, or anyone with chronic under-eye puffiness.</p>

