<!-- §11 How to use -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">How to Use the Cooling Gel Eye Mask</h2>

<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 1: Refrigerate Before First Use</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Place the Cooling Gel Eye Mask in your refrigerator for at least 2–3 hours before first use. Ideally, store it overnight to ensure optimal cooling. The gel should be cold to the touch but not frozen. Freezing can make the gel too stiff and potentially damage delicate under-eye skin. Refrigerate at 32–40°F.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 2: Lie Down and Position the Mask</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Get comfortable—lie in bed, on the couch, or sit back in a chair. Remove the chilled mask from the fridge and gently place it over your eyes. The soft gel should conform naturally to your eye contours without requiring pressure or adjustment. You should feel cool, refreshing contact, not cold burn.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 3: Relax for 15–20 Minutes</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Leave the mask on for 15–20 minutes while the cold therapy works. During this time, you can meditate, listen to music, read, or simply rest with your eyes closed. The gel will gradually warm to body temperature. You'll notice visible depuffing and lighter-looking dark circles by the end of the session.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 4: Remove and Refrigerate for Next Use</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Gently remove the mask and place it back in the refrigerator. No cleaning required unless you want to rinse with cool water and pat dry. The gel is reusable indefinitely with proper storage. Use daily for maintenance or as needed for acute puffiness. Results last a few hours; repeat in the evening if desired.</p>
  </div>
</div>

