<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How long does the gel stay cold?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The gel stays cold for approximately 20 minutes after removal from the refrigerator. This is the ideal window for a full depuffing treatment. After 20 minutes, the gel gradually warms to body temperature. Simply return it to the fridge for the next use—no refreeze needed for daily use.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Does it actually reduce puffiness and dark circles?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes, absolutely. Cold therapy constricts blood vessels and reduces inflammation under the eyes, which decreases swelling and the appearance of dark circles. Results are visible within 5–10 minutes of application. The effect is temporary (a few hours), but consistent daily use provides cumulative skin benefits and trains the lymphatic system to drain more efficiently.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Is it safe for sensitive skin?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Generally yes, but do a patch test first if you have extremely sensitive or reactive skin. The soft gel is gentle, but cold therapy can irritate some conditions. If you have rosacea, dermatitis, or cold sensitivity, consult a dermatologist before use. For most people, the mild cold is soothing and beneficial for inflammation.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I freeze it instead of just refrigerating?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Refrigeration is recommended. Freezing makes the gel too hard and can create ice crystals that damage delicate under-eye skin or cause cryoburn. Stick to 32–40°F (standard fridge temperature). If you do freeze it, allow it to partially thaw before applying.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How does it compare to the Weighted Eye Mask?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The Weighted Eye Mask ($55–$65, Vibe Score 78) focuses on sleep quality—its gentle pressure promotes relaxation and can improve sleep onset. The Cooling Gel Eye Mask ($42.11–$50.05, Vibe Score 73) focuses on depuffing and reducing puffiness with cold therapy. Choose Weighted if sleep is your goal; choose Cooling Gel if depuffing is priority.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How long does the gel last before needing replacement?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The gel is designed to be reusable indefinitely with proper care. There's no expiration date under normal storage (refrigerated, away from extreme heat or cold). The gel maintains its cooling properties for years. Just keep it clean and avoid puncturing the seal.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">What colors and options are available?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The Cooling Gel Eye Mask is available in six colors: Dark Blue, White-A, Green, Pink, Purple, and Sky Blue. You can also choose between Face Mask or Suit style options depending on your preference. All variants deliver the same cooling effect; color choice is purely aesthetic.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I use this for travel or on-the-go?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Not ideal for travel without a fridge. The mask requires continuous refrigeration to maintain cold. Hotel mini-fridges work, but prep time is needed. If you travel frequently, an ice-pack eye mask or cold spoons are more portable. This is best for home use or routines with consistent fridge access.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Will it work immediately when I put it on?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes. The chilled gel provides immediate cooling sensation. Within 5-10 minutes, you'll notice visible depuffing as blood vessels constrict and fluid retention decreases. The full effect becomes apparent around the 15-20 minute mark. Results are temporary but effective for morning routines.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I use it more than once a day?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes. Use it as many times as you need—morning, evening, or anytime for depuffing. Many users do morning and night sessions. Just return it to the fridge between uses. There's no limit to daily use. Some prefer to use it before important events for best appearance.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Does it work for other body parts?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">While designed for eyes, some users apply it to other facial areas for cooling relief. However, it's engineered specifically for the delicate under-eye area. Using it on other face areas may feel less effective due to different skin thicknesses. Stick to the eyes for best results.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">What if I wear makeup? Do I need to remove it first?</summary>
